sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant R as Researcher (Browser)
    participant NG as Nginx
    participant API as Flask API
    participant DB as MySQL
    participant RD as Redis

    Note over R,RD: 1. Researcher Login (same 2-step MFA flow)

    R->>NG: POST /api/auth/login {email, password}
    NG->>API: Forward request
    API->>DB: SELECT user WHERE email=... AND role=researcher
    DB-->>API: user row
    API->>API: bcrypt compare (timing-safe)
    API->>RD: SET mfa_pending_user_id in session
    API-->>R: 200 {message: "MFA required"}

    R->>NG: POST /api/auth/verify-mfa {totp_code}
    NG->>API: Forward request
    API->>RD: GET mfa_pending_user_id from session
    API->>API: pyotp.TOTP(mfa_secret).verify(totp_code)
    API->>RD: Regenerate session, SET user_id + role=researcher
    API->>DB: INSERT audit_log (login_success)
    API-->>R: 200 {role: "researcher", username}

    Note over R,RD: 2. Browse All Trials

    R->>NG: GET /api/researcher/trials
    NG->>API: require_role(researcher) verified
    API->>DB: SELECT all trials (all statuses, metadata only)
    DB-->>API: trials list
    API-->>R: 200 [trials metadata — no participant PII]

    Note over R,RD: 3. View Aggregate Cohort Statistics

    R->>NG: GET /api/researcher/trials/{trial_id}/stats
    NG->>API: require_role(researcher) verified
    API->>DB: SELECT trial WHERE trial_id=...
    DB-->>API: trial row
    API->>DB: COUNT participants WHERE trial_id AND consent_status=active
    API->>DB: COUNT participants WHERE trial_id AND withdrawal_triggered=true
    API->>DB: CALCULATE withdrawal_rate as percentage
    DB-->>API: aggregate counts
    API-->>R: 200 {total_enrolled, withdrawn, withdrawal_rate, spots_remaining}
    Note right of R: No PII, no pseudonym tokens,<br/>no individual records exposed

    Note over R,RD: 4. Logout

    R->>NG: POST /api/auth/logout
    NG->>API: Forward request
    API->>RD: DELETE session
    API->>DB: INSERT audit_log (logout)
    API-->>R: 200 {message: "Logged out"}
